Yum! I've made these mustard greens twice now and both times they turned out perfectly! I try to cook some sort of leafy green - swiss chard, kale, collard greens, or mustard greens a few times a week and, thanks to this recipe, both my husband and I have decided that mustard greens are our new favorite!

Rating: 4
This is an ideal recipe for someone who's not sure if he/she likes mustard greens (or any greens, actually). A straight forward method. If the mustard is fairly young, like what I was fortunate to have, you don't even need to remove many stems or ribs; just boil, squeeze, chop, and saute (or use a wok as I did; cooks that excess water out quite well) Be aware, though, that the boiling and heavy garlic flavor may cover up that mustard bite.

