Big hit! We bought mustard greens but had never prepared them before...we found this recipe super easy and yummy! One thing to note - one bunch of mustard greens cooks down to about a cup - just enough for one (if this is a feature dish) or maybe two (if there are multiple other side dishes) people.

Rating: 4
Wonderful, simple way to utilize a seasonal vegetable. Mustard greens can be bitter, however it seems that parboiling takes away the bitterness and leaves, in its place, the taste of nutty garlic. This lovely vegetable can be found at farmer's markets in the Fall season. Look up your nearest market and enjoy seasonal food at its finest.

